<p align="center" style="text-align:center"><span style="page:WordSection1"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:normal"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><b><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:Palatino"><span style="color:white">Additional Tips for Lab Interpretation</span></span></span></b></span></span></span></span></p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style="border-bottom:1px solid black; width:32%; padding:0in 7px 0in 7px; background-color:black; border-top:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black" valign="top">
<p align="center" style="text-align:center"><span style="page:WordSection1"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:normal"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:Palatino"><span style="color:white">SPEP/UPEP</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>
</td>
<td style="border-bottom:1px solid black; width:33%; padding:0in 7px 0in 7px; background-color:black; border-top:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-left:none" valign="top">
<p align="center" style="text-align:center"><span style="page:WordSection1"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:normal"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:Palatino"><span style="color:white">Free light chains (FLC)</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>
</td>
<td style="border-bottom:1px solid black; width:33%; padding:0in 7px 0in 7px; background-color:black; border-top:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-left:none" valign="top">
<p align="center" style="text-align:center"><span style="page:WordSection1"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:normal"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:Palatino"><span style="color:white">Urinalysis</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style="border-bottom:1px solid black; width:32%; padding:0in 7px 0in 7px; background-color:#e7e6e6; border-top:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black" valign="top">
<p><span style="page:WordSection1"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:normal"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:Palatino"><span style="color:black">Immunofixation determines clonality </span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>
<p><span style="page:WordSection1"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:normal"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:Palatino"><span style="color:black">(e.g. mono or polyclonal)</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>
<p> </p>
<p><span style="page:WordSection1"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:normal"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:Palatino"><span style="color:black">Monoclonal spike &gt;1.5 is indicative of underlying dyscrasia</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>
<p> </p>
<p><span style="page:WordSection1"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:normal"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:Palatino"><span style="color:black">Polyclonal spike suggests infectious, inflammatory, or reactive etiology</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>
</td>
<td style="border-bottom:1px solid black; width:33%; padding:0in 7px 0in 7px; border-top:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-left:none" valign="top">
<p><span style="page:WordSection1"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:normal"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:Palatino"><span style="color:black">Ratio of kappa/lambda &gt;3 highly suggestive of plasma cell dyscrasia</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>
<p> </p>
<p><span style="page:WordSection1"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:normal"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:Palatino"><span style="color:black">-Ratio 1.65 to 3 can be due to infectious process or renal insufficiency</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>
<p> </p>
<p><span style="page:WordSection1"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:normal"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:Palatino"><span style="color:black">Helpful in pts that only produce bence jones protein (FLC w/o heavy chain) which isn’t seen on SPEP</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>
</td>
<td style="border-bottom:1px solid black; width:33%; padding:0in 7px 0in 7px; background-color:#e7e6e6; border-top:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-left:none" valign="top">
<p><span style="page:WordSection1"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:normal"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:Palatino"><span style="color:black">Detects albumin, not light chains</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>
<p> </p>
<p><span style="page:WordSection1"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:normal"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:Palatino"><span style="color:black">In myeloma cast nephropathy, get negative dipstick since proteinuria is from FLC (i.e. Bence Jones proteinuria)</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>
<p> </p>
<p><span style="page:WordSection1"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:normal"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:Palatino"><span style="color:black">In AL amyloid, dipstick will be positive 2/2 albumin loss from nephrotic syndrome</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
